element.name: DESCRIPTION
element.text: This algorithm generates a new layer that indicates the time it takes the flow from each cell to reach the outlet of the basin

element.name: NETWORK
element.text: Channel network. If used, cells in the channel network will have a different flow speed that cells outside of it

element.name: RATIO
element.text: The ratio between the flow speed in channel cells and the on in cells not belonging to the channel network

element.name: OUTLET
element.text: The outlet point of the watershed

element.name: TIME
element.text: the values in the cells represent the time (in hours) that it takes the flow to reach the selected outlet point.The cells outside of the watershed have no data values.
